{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Giovanni bellini, pietà del museo correr 01.jpg | title=Dead Christ Supported by Two Angels | artist=Giovanni Bellini | year=c. 1460 | medium=Tempera on poplar panel | height_metric=74 | width_metric=50 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | museum=[[Museo Correr]] }} '''''Dead Christ Supported by Two Angels''''' is a painting by Italian Renaissance painter [[Giovanni Bellini]], created around 1460. It is housed in the [[Museo Correr]] in [[Venice]].
The panel is one of Bellini's earliest ''[[Pietà]]'' compositions, together with those in the [[Accademia Carrara]] of Bergamo and in the [[Museo Poldi Pezzoli]] of [[Milan]]. The date in the sepulchre's edge (1499) is [[apocriphal]], such as [[Albrecht Dürer]]'s [[monogram]].
==Sources== *{{cite book|first=Mariolina|last=Olivari|chapter=Giovanni Bellini|title=Pittori del Rinascimento|publisher= Scala|location=Florence|year=2007|isbn=888117099X}}
