{{Other uses|Gutai group#Method}}
[[File:ThomasSchweicker2.jpg|thumb|Self portrait by mouth and foot artist [[Thomas Schweicker]] (1540–1602)]] '''Mouth and foot painting''' is a technique to create [[drawing]]s, [[painting]]s and other works of art by maneuvering brushes and other tools with the mouth or foot. The technique is mostly used by artists who through illness, accident or congenital disability have no use of their hands. The [[Association of Mouth and Foot Painting Artists of the World|Association of Mouth and Foot Painting Artists]] (AMFPA) is a worldwide organization representing these artists.<ref name="vdmfkhist">{{cite web|title=History|url=https://www.vdmfk.com/en/about.html|website=www.vdmfk.com|publisher=[[Association of Mouth and Foot Painting Artists of the World]]|accessdate=18 February 2016}}</ref>
The brushes and tools that are used are ordinary artist's implements, but they may be modified in length or width.<ref>{{cite web|title=Artist Mouthpiece|url=https://www.arttreehouse.com/store/content/artist-mouthpiece|website=www.arttreehouse.com|publisher=The Art Treeshouse|accessdate=18 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Clayton|first1=Jon|title=My Specialist Equipment|url=http://www.jkcmouthartist.com/?page_id=100|website=www.jkcmouthartist.com|publisher=Jon Clayton|accessdate=18 February 2016}}</ref><ref name="mirror">{{cite web|last1=Smith|first1=Dominic|title=Paralysed artist paints amazing portrait of Thierry Henry's legendary goal celebration using only his mouth|date=25 July 2015|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/paralysed-artist-paints-amazing-portrait-6135328|website=www.mirror.co.uk|publisher=[[Daily Mirror]]|accessdate=18 February 2016}}</ref> Mouth painters hold the brush in their mouth or between their teeth and maneuver it with their tongue and cheek muscles.<ref name="sun">{{cite web|last1=Battle|first1=Bella|title=Incredible paintings are a work of mouth art|url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/news/4103893/Mouth-artist-Steve-Chambers-50-paints-with-the-brush-between-his-lips.html|website=www.thesun.co.uk|publisher=[[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]]|date=2 February 2012|accessdate=18 February 2016}}</ref> The paper or [[canvas]] is usually mounted vertically on an [[easel]]. Mouth painting is strenuous for neck and jaw muscles since the head has to perform the same back and forth movement as a hand does when painting.<ref>{{cite web|title=Squeezable Paint Brushes (Howard University)|url=http://aac-rerc.psu.edu/wordpressmu/RESNA-SDC/2014/05/31/squeezable-paint-brushes-howard-university/|website=www.aac-rerc.psu.edu|publisher=[[Rehabilitation Engineering and Assistive Technology Society of North America]]|accessdate=18 February 2016}}</ref><ref name="daily">{{cite web|last1=Winchester|first1=Levi|title=Watch: Woman born without fully-formed limbs creates stunning artwork using her mouth|url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/weird/487993/VIDEO-Woman-creates-art-with-her-mouth|date=10 July 2014|website=www.express.co.uk|publisher=[[Daily Express]]|accessdate=18 February 2016}}</ref> Foot painting can be done sitting on the floor, at a table or at an easel, as most foot painters use their toes with the same dexterity as people with hands use their fingers.<ref>{{cite web|title=An Amazing Feat – Artists Who Paint With Their Feet.|url=http://www.aucklandpodiatrist.co.nz/amazing-feat-artists-paint-feet/|date=20 November 2014|website=www.aucklandpodiatrist.co.nz|publisher=Healthy Steps Podiatry Ltd|accessdate=18 February 2016}}</ref><ref name="epigram">{{cite web|last1=Morris|first1=Millie|title=Creativity Despite Disability: Mouth and Foot Painting Artists|url=http://epigram.org.uk/arts/2014/11/creativity-despite-disability-mouth-and-foot-painting-artists|website=www.epigram.org.uk|publisher=[[Epigram (newspaper)|Epigram]]|date=30 November 2014|accessdate=18 February 2016}}</ref>
== Notable mouth and foot painters == *[[Simona Atzori]] *[[Sarah Biffen]] *[[Matthias Buchinger]] *[[John Carter (mouth artist)|John Carter]] *[[Louis Joseph César Ducornet]] *[[Alison Lapper]] *[[Edward Rainey]] *[[Thomas Schweicker]] *[[Steven L. Sles]] *[[Association of Mouth and Foot Painting Artists of the World#A. Erich Stegmann|Arnulf Erich Stegmann]] *[[Charles B. Tripp]] *[[Brom Wikstrom]]
